esqlQuery.esql:
// Alert on Kubernetes Pod NetworkNotReady events.
//
// What triggers this alert:
// Pod cannot start — CNI network plugin not ready or failed to configure networking.
//
// Common causes:
// CNI plugin issues (Calico/Cilium/etc), network policy conflicts, IP exhaustion.
//
// Action needed:
// Check CNI plugin status, verify network policies, review node networking.
//
// To scope to a namespace, add: AND `kubernetes.event.metadata.namespace` == "YOUR_NAMESPACE"
FROM metrics-kubernetes.event-*
| WHERE `kubernetes.event.involved_object.kind` == "Pod"
  AND `kubernetes.event.source.component` == "kubelet"
  AND `kubernetes.event.reason` == "NetworkNotReady"
| STATS doc_count = COUNT(*)
  BY `orchestrator.cluster.name`, `kubernetes.event.metadata.namespace`,
     `kubernetes.event.involved_object.name`, `kubernetes.event.involved_object.kind`,
     `kubernetes.event.reason`
| WHERE doc_count > 0
